In article <1992Jun19.074305.11826@qualcomm.com>, karn@chicago.qualcomm.com (Phil Karn) writes:
> Connect one of these things up to an FM receiver and digitize some
> noise and I'm sure you could extract some high quality random numbers
> from the low-order bits of the noise samples.

Gee -- a new hack -- broadcasting non-random static at someone's PC...

Seriously, there are a number of algorithms around that amplify the
randomness, as it were; it might be a good idea to use one of them
in conjunction with your noise source, to get a 50-50 split between
0 and 1 bits.
